# Engram CLI Environment Configuration

# GitHub Personal Access Token for accessing private Engram repositories
# Required for: engram-rs (private dependency)
#
# To generate a token:
# 1. Go to GitHub Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic)
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Grant the "repo" scope (full control of private repositories)
# 4. Copy the token and paste it below
#
# Configure Git to use this token:
#   git config --global url."https://${GITHUB_TOKEN}@github.com/".insteadOf "https://github.com/"
#
# Or set as environment variable before building:
#   export GITHUB_TOKEN=your_token_here
#   cargo build

GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token_here
